<item>
            <title>[SPARK-2454] Separate driver spark home from executor spark home</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2454</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The driver may not always share the same directory structure as the executors. It makes little sense to always re-use the driver&apos;s spark home on the executors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/1244/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/1244/&lt;/a&gt; is an open effort to fix this. However, this still requires us to set SPARK_HOME on all the executor nodes. Really we should separate this out into something like `spark.executor.home` and `spark.driver.home` rather than re-using SPARK_HOME everywhere.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12726876">SPARK-2454</key>
